node.text:
First Day of School: Pandemic Style ?
.
.
.
Livi started her first day at school, and it’s definitely not what we anticipated her going into Kindergarten would be, but of course, ‘Rona had to come make 2020 nothing that any of us could have anticipated ever. She’s doing Virtual Learning (since our county isn’t doing face-to-face; definitely have some bittersweet feels about it all ?), and already, it’s been so weird to have her at home doing school with her teachers on an iPad. Also, the challenges to communicate within a virtual classroom with a bunch of 5 and 6 year olds has been chaotic, basically exactly how you would expect that to go, and I feel for the teachers and kids alike. Thankful for teachers who are patiently working with and wrangling them! ??
.
.
.
This year isn’t what we thought it would be for us with school + working from home, but I’m hopeful that we can begin to flow into a nice routine after everyone acclimates to this new normal!
Wishing all of the parents out there Good Luck, prayers, and May the Odds Be Ever in Your Favor!?? (that’s the closest emoji I could find for that lol)
.
.
.
.

node.text:
My mom passed away 5 days before my first day of kindergarten... I am at the age she was & Abigale is the age I was in 1993 when she died. 

  What an eye opener its been this morning , as I got Abigale dressed for her big day and placed bows in her hair. I tried to take my time and not rush the morning, taking nothing for granted. 

I don’t remember much from my first day of kindergarten, but I do remember my mom not being there. As a mother now, I couldn’t imagine missing this huge milestone we’ve reached together. The last 5years have prepared us for today.

Abigale’s first day of kindergarten. 

Today you get to start a new chapter of your little life as you walk into that classroom and begin your first year of school. I am so proud of you, babygirl. Every fiber of my being radiates with pride for the person you are and the young woman you are becoming. You are clever, kind, courageous, and so, so beautiful.

Daddy & I love you beyond measure. We know you will be an exceptional student and an excellent friend to your classmates. If I could give you any advice as you embark on this new adventure, it would be this: always take the time to listen and learn. Listen to your teacher. Learn all you can, as knowledge is power. Listen to the people you meet and learn from the stories they tell you. Listen to your heart and never stop learning from your mistakes.

I know you will have fun today. I can't wait to see your beaming beautiful smile this afternoon and hear all about your first day!

I love you,
Mommy

For the past few months there's been a visible change in the pattern of traveling due to global pandemic. There was a time when travelling was considered to be a leisure activity which was much needed to escape the monotony of life. Travelling no more is a carefree activity, I remember there was a time when I used to sleep under the trees on bare grass; when I used to travel in congested subways, waiting in the long queues, eating from the road site stalls, hugging and shaking hands with the fellows. Now doing all this requires conscious effort. Accept it or not we all at some point will be & already are being affected by it. Masks & sanitizers are the new essentials for travelling which one may not think of forgetting while leaving home. Planning one’s trip, keeping in mind social distancing, won’t be as easy as it seems. Every cloud has a silver lining, so I am waiting for a time to come when holding the door knob of malls and shopping centers without worrying for the sanitizer will be the new cool. Will that time come? Will everything get back to normal? Or is this the new normal?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

I moved out of NYC this week.  My body got extraordinarily clear during quarantine - BE IN NATURE & STAY. 

And so it was a simple decision and happened quickly.  I listen to my body’s wisdom and trust her to guide me. 

I landed at my beloved lake in Stolkholm, NJ for the next 2 months then I’ll see what’s next. 

My first night here I turned off the lights to go to sleep and it was pitch black in my room.  I LOVE that and it’s practically impossible in the city.  I lay in bed and listen to a chorus of frogs and crickets.  It’s LOUD - they’ve got a-LOT to say and a wide range of pitches!  It’s so soothing on my system. 

As I write this, I’m sitting in bed and the rain is falling, my window is open and the cool breeze is filling the room.  I love the sound, the feel and the ease of it all. I’m going to swim and hike every day and take life a little slower and easier on this peak.

FITNESS HELPS FATIGUE. The burnout from this pandemic is real.  The physical fatigue, emotional fatigue and even decision fatigue. 
Most are exhausted and overwhelmed with a million things to do and think about.?
Exercise even if just 15-20 minutes a day is one of the great ways to ward off stress and burnout. ?
Aside from all of the physical health benefits, exercise makes you feel energized, increases the amount of energy you have during the day and also keeps your mood lifted and mind active and healthy. Exercise will help you sleep better too which is so needed now!?
**Check out my pandemic parenting guide** (link in bio) with more tips on how to fit in exercise, practice self-care, get more sleep and reduce stress during these times.. for you and your kids. 
And remember since there seems to be no end to each day, make sure to take breaks throughout the day too and do things that you enjoy. And it is OK to choose something that doesn’t feel exhausting - we are all exhausted enough. Do nothing ha! Stay well and safe all. Xx

A Placa de Mordida ou Placa Miorrelaxante  um aparelho mvel em acrlico que  colocado sobre os dentes.

O tratamento, que tem como objetivo principal diminuir a frequncia e intensidade da atividade muscular de apertamento e ranger dos dentes, tambm serve para proteger os dentes de desgastes e fraturas que aparecem junto com o problema.

A incidncia de casos de fratura dentria, desgastes, dores articulares, dentre outros muitos problemas, relacionados ao estresse e outros fatores, tem sido vistos com grande frequncia no dia a dia clnico. 

A Placa Miorrelaxante atua em conjunto com outras condutas clnicas,  fim de ajudar nossos pacientes.

node.text:
Flowers to brighten your Monday feed! This weekend was seriously exactly what I’ve been craving and needed! ??
Spent the weekend (safely ? ) in Pittsburgh hanging with my bestie, @ablessedstressedmama ! It’s been wayyyy too long! We went for a hike, went flower picking, had a fire, ate great food, & had a photo shoot with the one & only @gossboss_photovideo 
I feel soooo refreshed and ready to tackle the rest of August & the beginning of the school year. I’ve been in such a bad mind space and funk ( as I’m sure the majority of us feel, thanks #pandemic2020). But getting to chat allll weekend with my best girl, getting a mental break from home & the kids, I feel like a whole new person. ? I don’t ever take time for myself and I hate leaving my kids. It’s not easy for me to just go do something for myself, I’m not wired that way, but it’s soooo important for my mental health. So thanks for an amazing weekend, girls!!!! ???
Happy Monday, friends! ?

I didn't do this before because after working in health care in engineering and with infection control,well, how things are spread are mind blowing.  Anywho,  I don't touch babies (or any child) without being given permission..even if it's a simple rub on the head. I had a friend thank me before this because another person gave me crap for not touching the new baby...seriously?! I haven't even washed my hands. I'm not exposing this child to my germs! I think we've all learned a lot these past few months. With back to school fast approaching I realize that many things we used to do that were ok before.. are so NOT ok now!?????????
?????????
The old.. 2 second rule is one of those for sure!  If you aren't aware of what the 2 second rule is, let me explain.?????????
?????????
If you are eating a snack lets say.. such as goldfish crackers.. and one of those delicious cheesy crackers say, falls on the ground.. you would say to yourself.. oh no! 2 second rule!! Pick up the cracker from the floor, maybe blow on it for a second and then EAT IT. That's right, off the floor.?????????
?????????
Maybe before that was border line OK to do. Admit it.. you've totally done it! ?????????
?????????
Now in a world with Covid-19 it's really NOT ok. Phrases like.. 2 second rule, and just rub some dirt on it are not going to fly.  It's going to take a little time, but we'll need to change our language and update our mindset to protect ourselves and everyone else.?????????
?????????
Do you agree? What phrases do you think are so 2019? Which phrases do you plan on NOT passing down to your kids? Share in the comments below!?????????

node.text:
A total of 11 students filed a petition against conducting the JEE and NEET examinations, to which the supreme court denied the plea. Justice Arun Mishra said that postponing the exams will mkae the students lose their academic year and put their careers in peril. He also added that life should go on amidst covid 19 and questioned how exams should be conducted.
Solicitor General Tushar Mehta appearing for NTA said that the exams will have to be conducted and that adequate precautions will be taken for conducting these tests.
The students who filed the petition said that by conducting the JEE Main 2020, JEE Advanced 2020 and NEET 2020 during a pandemic is a violation of the Right to Life of several lakhs students in india. JEE Main 2020 is to be held online from September 1 to 6 while NEET 2020 for admission to undergraduate medical courses is slated to be held offline on September 13 across 161 exam centres in India.

Source-https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/india/jee-main-2020-neet-2020-exam-dates-supreme-court-dismisses-plea-to-postp-5716311.html

node.text:
As schools will be reopening soon, a lot of  parents are trying to figure out whether they should send their kids or not. We are fortunate enough to live in a country where we have the option of pursuing 100% distance learning if we wish. 
?
In the case of attending in person school,  kids would get some sense of normalcy (i.e. “new normal“), interact, be around their peers once again and finally get some proper learning (I think).
?
The downside is that we’re in the midst of a global pandemic and even countries which were settling in, are now seeing their numbers go up. 
?
I am very grateful to live in the UAE ?? where the government has instilled strict measures and rules to be followed and consequently our numbers have not gone completely out of control alhumdullilah (so far). 
?
In these uncertain times, what is YOUR family planning to do in terms of schooling? If you are in a country where schools have reopened, graciously share your experiences! ? 
.
.
.
.
